{{Cnote2|b|He was mentioned as "Liudewitus, dux Pannoniae inferioris" in the [[Frankish Annals]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Balcanoslavica|volume=5-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-lU8AAAAIAAJ|year=1977|page=114|quote=The report refers to the uprising of Liudewitus, dux Pannoniae inferioris (Ljudevit Posavski), which was joined by the inhabitants of Carniola (Annales regni Francorum, ad a. 818 — 823).}}</ref> This title is translated as "Duke of Lower Pannonia".<ref name="Luthar2008">{{cite book|author=Oto Luthar|title=The Land Between: A History of Slovenia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=G9tDboBJ70EC&pg=PA109|year=2008|publisher=Peter Lang|isbn=978-3-631-57011-1|pages=109–}}</ref> In older Croatian historiography, his title was claimed to have been "Duke of Pannonian Croatia", which is erraneous, as it is anachronistic. The Croat ethnonym was first mentioned in the late 9th century.<ref>{{cite journal | ref = Gračanin-2008 | url = http://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=57788&lang=en | language = Croatian | title = Od Hrvata pak koji su stigli u Dalmaciju odvojio se jedan dio i zavladao Ilirikom i Panonijom: Razmatranja uz DAI c. 30, 75-78 | first = Hrvoje | last = Gračanin | journal = History Teaching | issn = 1334-1375 | publisher = Croatian Historical Society | volume =  VI | number = 11 (1) |date=June 2008 | accessdate = 2012-07-27}}</ref> }}
